  "articleSummary": "This analytical article argues that AWS EC2 `i3` instances equipped with NVMe SSDs deliver the optimal price-to-I/O performance ratio for cloud storage, despite AWS’s typically complex pricing structures. Focusing on the `i3.large` and `i3.2xlarge` instance types, the author presents benchmark data highlighting ultra-fast storage speeds while cautioning that actual network throughput frequently underperforms advertised limits. Written in a practical, data-driven tone with a head-to-head comparison framing, the piece targets cloud architects, DevOps engineers, and developers evaluating infrastructure for performance-intensive workloads. The analysis relies on interactive cost charts and real-world network tests to guide readers toward optimized cloud configurations.",
